{"word":"ἀναβαθμός","slug":"ἀναβαθμός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀναβαϑμός, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀνά\">ἀνά</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:βαθμός\">βαθμός</a></el> ‘step’, as compound <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀναβαίνω\">ἀναβαίνω</a></el>] ‘a going up’ or ‘an ascent’ <i>step:</i> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pl.\">pl.</a> <b><i>flight of steps/stairs,</i></b> the ‘steps’ leading up from Jerusalem’s temple to the tower of Antonia <b><a href='B:510 21:35'>Ac 21:35</a>, <a href='B:510 21:40'>40</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀνάβα\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀναβαίνω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}